# hexa-lang /.raw — L0 universal rules (parser-owner self-host)
# SSOT — 이 파일이 hexa-lang 의 root SSOT.
# 포맷 스펙: self/raw_loader.hexa (이 repo 가 owner)
# 검증: ./build/hexa_stage0 self/raw_cli.hexa verify
#
# 포맷:
#   raw <num> <status> "<name>"
#     <key> <value...>
#     ...
#   (빈 줄 = rule 구분, # = 주석, 같은 key 여러 줄 = 배열)
#
# 모든 hive .raw rules 를 inherit (cross-repo self-format#inherit) — 이 파일은 hexa-lang local 만 선언.

raw 1 live "hexa-lang self-host fixpoint — parser-owner consumes own format"
  slug hexa-lang-self-host
  enforce self/raw_cli.hexa verify
  decl self/raw_loader.hexa
  scope hexa-lang/.raw + hexa-lang/.own + hexa-lang/.doc
  why hexa-lang implements raw_loader.hexa — the parser FOR self-format DSL. Hosting zero canonical .raw at root = meta-circular violation. raw_loader.hexa MUST round-trip parse this file as the implementation acceptance test.
  proof self/raw_cli.hexa verify --target hexa-lang/.raw
  proof self/raw_cli.hexa verify --target hexa-lang/.own
  proof self/raw_cli.hexa verify --target hexa-lang/.doc

raw 2 live "naming reconciliation — .commands → .command (canonical)"
  slug naming-canonical
  status convention
  scope .commands → .command, .chain (chain-kind extension), .raw-ref (sync metadata)
  why hexa-lang invented .commands (plural) before canonical .command (singular) was promoted across hive. Reconciliation deferred until consumers (tool/cmd_*.hexa handlers) are repointed.
  defer-until phase-3 of F1 bootstrap (after .raw + .own + .doc land)
  follow-up rename .commands → .command + update tool/install_os.hexa references
